pullRequests.title: set maximum burst of elastic autoscaling to 30
pullRequests.description:
### Explanation of changes made:

Change the `maximumElasticWorkerCount` of Stage and Production App Service Plans to be `30` instead of the default `5`.
This correlates to the `Maximum Burst Amount` option in Azure Portal.

### Reason for changes made:

This setting acts as the "maximum instance count" for this app service plan. In early march when elastic scale premium autoscaling was reintroduced to MCSApi, this setting was left out of the configuration. This caused MCSAPI app services to never scale beyond 5 instances, even during heavy loads like performance testing.

Because each app service plan only has 1 app service inside it, we can safely set the `Maximum Burst Amount` to be equal to the maximum instance count we pay for our app service plan.

In the future, we also hope to set the minimum elastic instance count through terraform as well. This is not currently supported by the `azurerm` provider, though I will make an issue on their repository to show our interest in them making one. :D

### API Endpoint(s) affected:

None

### What changes were made to the requests and/or responses of the API endpoint(s)?

None

### What is the link to the CGR? Please paste the link here and link the work item in this PR.

https://dev.azure.com/exelontfs/EU-Change%20Governance/_workitems/edit/2310215/

pullRequests.title: 3/18 ZDT Release
pullRequests.description:
### Explanation of changes made:

[DevSecOps]
- Remove `azapi` module references to provision `elasticScaleEnabled` variable on shared app service plan
- Replaced with `premium_plan_auto_scale_enabled tfva`r, which is being sent directly into the `serviceplan` module
- Updated minimum `azurerm` to `v4.21.1`
-- Lock down `azurerm` so it no longer uses the latest version
- Updated `serviceplan` module to `v3.0.2` from `v1.0.10`
-- Module update PR: https://github.com/exeloncorp/terraform-azurerm-serviceplan/pull/4 
-- Added `devops_tf_id` tfvar since it is a requirement of this new module version
- Reformated all affected `.tf` files for readability (terraform format)
- Add `terraform.lock.hcl` to repository so provider versions have less flexibility during pipeline runs

Additionally...
- Update environment variables to prevent AppInsights listener from being lost

[Customer Hardening]
- Update EUDAPI APIM API policy such that calling `registration/validate` now invokes the `ValidateReCaptcha_DeprecationWarning` APIM policy fragment.

### Reason for changes made:

[DevSecOps]
There is a bug introduced recently with the `azapi` provider that made updating the `elasticScaleEnabled` flag on Azure App Service Plans inconsistent. This caused our release pipeline to fail multiple times in a row in an "Operation Locked" state, which wouldn't be resolved until after several redeployments and would creep it's way back upon next deployment.

This PR fixes this issue by avoiding the `azapi` provider all together and instead passing the variable in to the now updated `serviceplan` module. `azurerm` now supports our new variable officially, so we no longer need to use `azapi` to skirt around it.

Additionally, this PR also fixes a regression introduced in January Monthly release where upon every MCSAPI release, AppInsights would stop listening to the appservice.

[Customer Hardening]
...

### API Endpoint(s) affected:

[DevSecOps]
N/A

[Customer Hardening]
- `registration/validate`

[DevSecOps]

pullRequests.title: [DevOps] Fix issue with stage (and prod) release pipeline failing inconsistently due to `enable_elastic_scale` tfvar
pullRequests.description:
### Explanation of changes made:

- Remove `azapi` module references to provision `elasticScaleEnabled` variable on shared app service plan
- Replaced with `premium_plan_auto_scale_enabled` tfvar, which is being sent directly into the `serviceplan` module
- Updated minimum AzureRM to `v4.21.1`
-- Lock down AzureRM so it no longer uses the latest version
- Updated `serviceplan` module to `v3.0.2` from `v1.0.10`
-- Module update PR: https://github.com/exeloncorp/terraform-azurerm-serviceplan/pull/4
-- Added `devops_tf_id` tfvar since it is a requirement of this new module version
- Reformated all affected .tf files for readability (`terraform format`)
- Add `terraform.lock.hcl` to repository so provider versions have less flexibility during pipeline runs

### Reason for changes made:

There is a bug introduced recently with the `azapi` provider that made updating the `elasticScaleEnabled` flag on Azure App Service Plans inconsistent. This caused our release pipeline to fail multiple times in a row in an "Operation Locked" state, which wouldn't be resolved until after several redeployments and would creep it's way back upon next deployment.

This PR fixes this issue by avoiding the `azapi` provider all together and instead passing the variable in to the now updated `serviceplan` module. `azurerm` now supports our new variable officially, so we no longer need to use `azapi` to skirt around it.
